rces%20have%20suffered%20at%20least%20197%20damaged%20and%20destroyed%20vehicles%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Wednesday%20Institute%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20War%2C%20a%20Washington%20DC-based%20think%20tank%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.understandingwar.org%2Fbackgrounder%2Frussian-offensive-campaign-assessment-november-1-2023-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20citing%20open-source%20geolocation%20project%20GeoConfirmed.%2099%20vehicles%20were%20lost%20in%20the%20first%20wave%20of%20assaults%20between%20October%209%20and%2013%2C%20and%20another%2094%20were%20lost%20between%20October%2014%20and%2023.%20Since%20then%2C%20four%20additional%20vehicles%20have%20been%20confirmed%20lost.%20Another%2018%20are%20considered%20potentially%20wrecked.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGeoConfirmed%20characterized%20the%20Russian%20effort%20near%20Avdiivka%20as%20the%20costliest%20Russian%20effort%20thus%20far%20in%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20ISW%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20figures%20are%20staggering%2C%20especially%20when%20compared%20to%20Ukraine's%20losses%20over%20months%20along%20another%20part%20of%20the%20front%20line%20in%20the%20south%20near%20Zaporizhzhia%2C%20where%20Ukrainian%20forces%20have%20been%20pushing%20against%20fortified%20Russian%20defenses%20as%20part%20of%20the%20ongoing%20counteroffensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Ukrainians%20lost%20a%20little%20above%20200%20vehicles%2C%20that%20we%20can%20observe%20and%20confirm%2C%20in%20southern%20Ukraine%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%20over%20the%20course%20of%20four%20or%20five%20months%20of%20operation%2C%26quot%3B%20George%20Barros%2C%20the%20geospatial-intelligence%20team%20lead%20and%20a%20Russia%20analyst%20at%20ISW%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0It%20took%20Russia%20roughly%20three%20weeks%20fighting%20for%20Avdiivka%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20comparison%20paints%20a%20sobering%20picture%20of%20the%20costs%20of%20the%20assault%20for%20Russia.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20conclude%20now%20that%20this%20is%20by%20far%20the%20most%20costly%20Russian%20assault%20during%20three%20weeks%20for%20one%20city%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Barros%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20an%20undertaking%20that%20lasted%20three%20weeks%20just%20for%20one%20town%2C%20this%20is%20the%20most%20costly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20army%20soldiers%20of%20the%2022nd%20brigade%20during%20tank%20training%20as%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20continues%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20October%2029%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654548ec3cc84b4dfafc4d85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20army%20soldiers%20of%20the%2022nd%20brigade%20during%20tank%20training%20as%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20continues%20in%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine%20on%20October%2029%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EDiego%20Herrera%20Carcedo%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Russia's%20losses%20in%20Avdiivka%20go%20well%20beyond%20its%20vehicles.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-bloody-fight-in-avdiivka-has-slaughtered-its-forces-milbloggers-2023-10%5C%22%3Eslaughter%20of%20mostly%20inexperienced%20troops%3C%2Fa%3E%20rushed%20to%20forward%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20the%20battle%20for%20Bakhmut%20earlier%20this%20year.%20Russia%20has%20again%20resorted%20to%20its%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20wave%20tactics%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20involve%20throwing%20waves%20of%20troops%20at%20the%20front%20line%20with%20poor%20training%20and%20little%20equipment.%20It's%20not%20an%20entirely%20ineffective%20strategy%2C%20but%20casualty%20numbers%20soar%20and%20it%20results%20in%20substantial%20carnage.%20A%20Ukrainian%20military%20spokesperson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-disregards-losses-presses-ukraines-avdiivka-2023-10-25%2F%5C%22%3Etold%20Reuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20late%20October%20that%20over%20a%20period%20of%20six%20days%2C%20forces%20fighting%20for%20Russia%20saw%20an%20estimated%202%2C500%20soldiers%20killed%20and%20wounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20assault%20forces%20are%20facing%20a%20lethal%20combination%20of%20Ukrainian%20weapons%2C%20including%20first-person%20view%20(FPV)%20drones%2C%20anti-tank%20missiles%2C%20artillery%2C%20and%20mortars%20able%20to%20wreck%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20these%20setbacks%2C%20Russia%20has%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-troops-avdiivka-taking-heavy-losses-threaten-pocket-ukrainian-troops-2023-10%5C%22%3Emade%20some%20advances%20in%20Avdiivka%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20geolocated%20footage%20collected%20by%20ISW.%20One%20Ukrainian%20journalist%20said%20that%20while%20Russia%20is%20suffering%20heavy%20losses%20in%20the%20fight%2C%20its%20movement%20along%20a%20railway%20track%20that%20could%20allow%20them%20to%20regroup%20and%20concentrate%20forces%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20very%20serious%20threat%20that%20needs%20maximum%20attention.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAvdiivka%20has%20been%20largely%20ruined%20by%20constant%20fighting%2C%20but%20the%20devastated%20area%20may%20not%20be%20entirely%20pointless%20to%20Russian%20forces%2C%20or%20Russian%20leadership.%20The%20loss%20of%20Avdiivka%20would%20push%20Ukraine%20back%20from%20the%20threshold%20of%20Donetsk%2C%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20launch%20attacks%20to%20retake%20the%20area.%20Russia%20would%20also%20be%20able%20to%20establish%20supply%20routes%20and%20connect%20main%20routes%20between%20its%20occupied%20territory%20if%20it%20had%20control%20of%20Avdiivka.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20the%20win%20could%20be%20valuable%20politically.%20Beyond%20Bakhmut%2C%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20a%20Pyrrhic%20victory%20at%20best%2C%20Russia%20has%20won%20few%20battlefield%20victories.%20And%20to%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20it%20has%20seen%20a%20few%20tumultuous%20incidents%20occur%20throughout%20the%20year%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Wagner%20Group%20mutiny.%20With%20a%20presidential%20election%20coming%20in%20early%202024%2C%20it's%20possible%20that%20Putin%20has%20decided%20to%20prioritize%20taking%20Avdiivka%20in%20order%20to%20maintain%20the%20appearance%20of%20control%20and%20demonstrate%20capability%20as%20a%20leader%20to%20Russians%20watching%20friends%20and%20family%20die%20in%20a%20war%20he%20aggressively%20initiated%20and%20has%20had%20to%20conduct%20unwelcome%20mobilizations%20to%20feed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-paying-for-assault-on-avdiivka-heavy-vehicle-losses-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699044867000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654542a63cc84b4dfafc4179%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-paying-for-assault-on-avdiivka-heavy-vehicle-losses-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russian%20forces%20have%20launched%20a%20fierce%20offensive%20attempting%20to%20capture%20Avdiivka%2C%20resulting%20in%20bloody%20fighting%20and%20heavy%20losses.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40insider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-paying-for-assault-on-avdiivka-heavy-vehicle-losses-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Abigail%20Breslin%20Refused%20to%20Work%20Alone%20With%20Aaron%20Eckhart%20on%20Thriller%20Due%20to%20%E2%80%98Demeaning%2C%20Unprofessional%E2%80%99%20Behavior%2C%20Lawsuit%20Alleges%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699044506000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-conte