jpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Amazon%20driver%20uses%20a%20custom%20Rivian%20electric%20delivery%20vehicle.%3Cp%3EMustafa%20Hussain%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EAmazon%20delivery%20drivers%20are%20hired%20by%20third-party%20courier%20companies%20known%20as%20Delivery%20Service%20Partners.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EDSP%20companies%20are%20responsible%20for%20Amazon%20driver%20wages%20and%20benefits.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EDrivers%20have%20between%20170%20and%20350%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-double-same-day-delivery-sites-increase-delivery-speed-2023-7%5C%22%3EAmazon%20orders%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20deliver%20per%20shift%2C%20depending%20on%20their%20location.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%20data-pm-slice%3D%5C%221%201%20%5B%5D%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20doorsteps%20would%20look%20different%20without%20Amazon's%20275%2C000%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-delivery-driver-jobs-what-its-like-long-shift-hours-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelivery%20drivers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-pm-slice%3D%5C%221%201%20%5B%5D%5C%22%3EDrivers%20typically%20have%20between%20170%20and%20350%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-drivers-interview-giant-war-between-them-and-company-packages-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epackages%20to%20deliver%3C%2Fa%3E%20per%20shift%2C%20depending%20on%20their%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20like%20Uber%20and%20Doordash%20drivers%2C%20Amazon%20delivery%20drivers%20are%20not%20employees%20of%20the%20company%20they%20work%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20drivers%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-controls-delivery-drivers-without-paying-wages-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindependent%20subcontractors%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20third-party%20courier%20companies%20known%20as%20Delivery%20Service%20Partners.%20These%20logistics%20firms%20work%20out%20of%20Amazon%20shipment%20facilities%20and%20employ%20the%20drivers%2C%20while%20Amazon%20provides%20drivers%20with%20branded%20uniforms%20and%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20much%20are%20Amazon%20drivers%20paid%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIndividual%20DSP%20companies%20are%20in%20charge%20of%20Amazon%20driver%20wages%20and%20benefits%20such%20as%20healthcare%20and%20paid%20time%20off.%20Both%20pay%20and%20benefits%20can%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20location.%20Some%20DSP%20drivers%20earn%20hourly%20wages%20and%20work%20part-time%20or%20full-time%20hours.%20The%20average%20hourly%20rate%20for%20Amazon%20drivers%20is%20%2419.48%2C%20according%20to%20Indeed.%20Drivers%20can%20work%20up%20to%2010%20hours%20daily%2C%20four%20to%20five%20days%20per%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20drivers%20earn%20salaries%20and%20work%20a%20typical%2040-hour%20week.%20According%20to%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20annual%20salaries%20for%20Amazon%20drivers%20can%20range%20between%20%2429%2C500%20and%20%2440%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20is%20the%20job%20like%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-delivery-drivers-reveal-claims-of-disturbing-work-conditions-2018-8%5C%22%3EAmazon%20delivery%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20responsible%20for%20last-mile%20deliveries%20or%20getting%20packages%20to%20their%20final%20destinations%20%E2%80%94%20customers'%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20beginning%20of%20each%20shift%2C%20drivers%20load%20packages%20from%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-warehouse-expansion-slowed-still-towers-over-competitors-2022-12%5C%22%3EAmazon%20fulfillment%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20their%20vans%20or%20trucks.%20Large%20packages%20are%20loaded%20individually%2C%20while%20small%20packages%20come%20in%20large%20totes.%20Each%20package%20has%20a%20code%2C%20which%20tells%20the%20driver%20what%20order%20to%20load%20so%20that%20the%20first%20one%20to%20go%20in%20is%20the%20last%20to%20be%20delivered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrivers%20tend%20to%20have%20consistent%20routes%20based%20on%20their%20area%2C%20so%20they%20deliver%20to%20the%20same%20customers%20weekly.%20In%20a%20blog%20post%20for%20Amazon%2C%20one%20driver%20who%20worked%209%20to%205%20said%20he%20made%20anywhere%20from%20170%20to%20190%20stops%20and%20delivered%20about%20250%20to%20300%20packages%20daily%20in%20the%20South%20Boston%20suburbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20do%20you%20become%20an%20Amazon%20driver%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20become%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Famazon%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20driver%2C%20you%20must%20apply%20for%20open%20positions%20at%20a%20DSP%20in%20your%20area%20and%20have%20a%20valid%20driver's%20license%20in%20your%20current%20state.%20The%20job%20can%20be%20physically%20demanding%2C%20so%20you'll%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20haul%20heavy%20packages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20are%20an%20Amazon%20driver%20or%20fulfillment%20center%20employee%20and%20would%20like%20to%20share%20your%20experience%2C%20please%20email%20this%20reporter%20at%20jortakales%40insider.com%20or%20text%20(646)%20768-4742%20using%20the%20Signal%20app.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-delivery-driver%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699043762000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6544bb6336d588dc55c9ebf3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-delivery-driver%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amazon%20delivery%20drivers%20are%20hired%20by%20third-party%20courier%20companies%20known%20as%20Delivery%20Service%20Partners%2C%20responsible%20for%20a%20driver's%20salary%20and%20benefits.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jortakales%40insider.com%20(Jennifer