0every%20task%20themselves%2C%20including%20designing%20glasses%2C%20packing%20them%20up%2C%20and%20doing%20their%20own%20bookkeeping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20felt%20manageable%20when%20they%20were%20shipping%20a%20few%20pairs%20of%20glasses%20a%20day.%20But%20when%20thousands%20of%20new%20orders%20started%20coming%20in%20daily%2C%20they%20decided%20it%20was%20time%20to%20bring%20on%20help.%20%26quot%3BWe%20realized%20that%20we%20couldn't%20do%20it%20all%20and%20we%20were%20burning%20ourselves%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20scaling%20down%20their%20involvement%20in%20day-to-day%20operations%2C%20they've%20been%20able%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20building%20brand%20awareness%20and%20securing%20larger%20deals%2C%20leading%20to%20collaborations%20with%20brands%20like%20Nickelodeon%20and%20Harlem%20Haberdashery.%20%26quot%3BMy%20goal%20is%20to%20have%20the%20company%20run%20with%20or%20without%20us%20%E2%80%94%20we%20need%20to%20be%20front-facing%20to%20make%20the%20deals%20and%20get%20the%20distribution%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Moseley%2C%20who's%20owned%20a%20Marco's%20Pizza%20franchise%20since%202018%2C%20said%20that%20hiring%20extra%20help%20was%20instrumental%20in%20her%20business'%20success.%20When%20her%20store%20was%20struggling%20financially%20early%20on%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20bring%20on%20a%20general%20manager%20with%20experience%20in%20the%20pizza%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investment%20paid%20off.%20%26quot%3BI%20noticed%20an%20immediate%20impact%20in%20sales%20going%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Moseley%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20turned%20me%20from%20being%20in%20the%20red%20into%20the%20black%20in%20less%20than%20two%20months.%26quot%3B%20She%20has%20since%20opened%20five%20other%20locations%20with%20that%20early%20hire%20overseeing%20all%20her%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%2C%20Green%2C%20and%20Moseley%20shared%20their%20best%20advice%20for%20hiring%20to%20scale%20a%20small%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFavor%20experience%20over%20affordability%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoseley%20said%20she%20quickly%20realized%20the%20general%20manager%20she'd%20initially%20hired%20didn't%20have%20the%20management%20experience%20her%20store%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoseley%20decided%20to%20expand%20her%20budget%20%E2%80%94%20dipping%20into%20her%20personal%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20to%20hire%20someone%20more%20skilled.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20wanted%20to%20get%20somebody%20with%20a%20wealth%20of%20pizza%20experience%20to%20take%20me%20to%20the%20next%20level%2C%20it%20was%20going%20to%20cost%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226229%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Headshot%20of%20Stephanie%20Moseley%20in%20her%20pizza%20shop%20wearing%20a%20green%20collared%20shirt%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65412bb9284fe8aac5233af1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224672%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStephanie%20Moseley%20owns%20Marco's%20Pizza%20stores.%3Cp%3EMarco's%20Pizza%2FBlake%20J%20Discher%2C%20Firefly%20Studios%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20and%20Green%20have%20relied%20on%20using%20contractors%20to%20access%20skilled%20talent%20on%20a%20budget.%20Instead%20of%20focusing%20on%20price%20when%20vetting%20potential%20hires%2C%20they%20focus%20on%20understanding%20the%20value%20the%20contractors%20could%20provide.%20The%20best%20way%20they've%20found%20to%20identify%20contractors%20who'll%20meet%20their%20needs%20is%20by%20asking%20for%20referrals%20from%20other%20business%20owners%20and%20getting%20references%20from%20each%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20they're%20charging%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20or%20they're%20charging%20bare%20minimum%2C%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20they%20are%20a%20match%20to%20our%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFind%20people%20who%20care%20about%20your%20mission%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESmall-business%20owners%20should%20look%20for%20employees%20who%20understand%20their%20company's%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoseley%20said%20her%20winning%20general%20manager%20stood%20out%20because%20he%20was%20passionate%20about%20the%20store's%20success.%20She%20said%20she%20knew%20this%20was%20the%20case%20when%20he%20volunteered%20to%20take%20a%20lower%20salary%20than%20what%20she'd%20offered%20him%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20he'd%20asked%20about%20the%20store's%20finances%20and%20concluded%20its%20earnings%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20support%20that%20salary.%20He%20offered%20to%20work%20his%20way%20up%20to%20a%20higher%20salary%20as%20the%20store's%20revenue%20improved.%20%26quot%3BThat%20just%20spoke%20oodles%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20integrity%20%E2%80%94%20that%20he%20wasn't%20just%20going%20to%20take%20my%20money%20but%20he%20was%20going%20to%20perform%20the%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20and%20Green%20said%20they%20struggled%20to%20find%20candidates%20who%20they%20felt%20understood%20their%20company%20and%20what%20made%20it%20stand%20out%20%E2%80%94%20for%20instance%2C%20the%20founders%20wanted%20their%20marketing%20to%20highlight%20their%20desire%20to%20make%20eyewear%20designed%20specifically%20for%20people%20of%20color.%20They%20said%20that%20now%20they%20ask%20a%20candidate%20to%20explain%20what%20value%20they'd%20add%20to%20the%20company%20to%20get%20a%20peek%20into%20how%20they%20think%20and%20filter%20for%20candidates%20who've%20researched%20and%20understand%20their%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDon't%20be%20afraid%20to%20part%20ways%20when%20hires%20aren't%20a%20fit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20how%20much%20vetting%20you%20do%2C%20you'll%20likely%20make%20the%20wrong%20hire%20at%20some%20point.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20be%20afraid%20to%20let%20somebody%20go%20if%20it's%20not%20working%20out%2C%20because%20it's%20your%20money%20and%20it's%20your%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Green%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20she%20and%20Harris%20typically%20decid