%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshowcase%2Fcelebrate%20achievements%20of%20the%20NDA%20government%20during%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20through%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CViksit%20Bharat%20Sankalp%20Yatra%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ENovember%2020%2C%202023%20to%20January%2025%2C%202024.%20The%20yatra%20would%20traverse%20765%20districts%20in%20the%20country%2C%20covering%202.69%20lakh%20gram%20panchayats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%20on%20October%206%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20had%20subpoenaed%20the%20armed%20forces%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdefence-ministry-selfie-points-narendra-modi%5C%22%3Epromote%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20achievements%20in%20various%20fields.%20As%20per%20the%20directions%20issued%2C%20the%20armed%20forces%20will%20create%20822%20geo-tagged%20%E2%80%98selfie%20points%E2%80%99%20in%20public%20places%20across%20the%20country%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshowcase%20good%20works%20done%20in%20defence%E2%80%9D%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20%E2%80%9Cenables%20the%20people%20to%20get%20the%20feeling%20of%20being%20a%20part%20of%20the%20initiative.%E2%80%9D%20The%20additional%20director%20general%20(media%20and%20communications)%2C%20MoD%20issued%20a%20Standard%20Operating%20Procedure%20(SOP)%20which%20recommends%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20%E2%80%98selfie%20points%E2%80%99%20may%20contain%20a%20giant-sized%20picture%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%E2%80%9D%20Another%20order%20was%20issued%20by%20the%20MoD%20on%20October%209%2C%202023%20instructing%20soldiers%20on%20annual%20leave%20to%20promote%20government%20schemes%2C%20designating%20them%20as%20%E2%80%9Csoldier-ambassadors.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13164820%2FScreenshot-2023-10-13-at-4.46.40.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13164820%2FScreenshot-2023-10-13-at-4.46.40.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13164820%2FScreenshot-2023-10-13-at-4.46.40-300x143.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13164820%2FScreenshot-2023-10-13-at-4.46.40-1024x488.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-679966%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22572%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20collage%20of%20the%20visual%20aids%20offered%20by%20the%20defence%20ministry%20to%20organisations%20and%20departments%20under%20it%2C%20to%20illustrate%20how%20the%20selfie%20points%20should%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20extraordinary%20commandeering%20of%20civil%20services%20and%20the%20armed%20forces%20for%20propaganda%20at%20one%20go%20is%20obviously%20aimed%20at%20creating%20a%20positive%20public%20perception%20of%20the%20BJP%20government%20in%20general%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20in%20particular%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20general%20elections%20to%20parliament%2C%20due%20in%20April-May%2C%202024.%20Looked%20at%20from%20several%20dimensions%2C%20this%20is%20a%20dangerous%20move.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFirst%20is%20the%20federal%20dimension.%20Article%201%20of%20the%20constitution%20says%20%E2%80%98India%2C%20that%20is%20Bharat%2C%20shall%20be%20a%20Union%20of%20States.%E2%80%9D%20The%20core%20objective%20of%20the%20constitution%20was%20to%20ensure%20national%20unity%20and%20integrity%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20performing%20the%20task%20of%20socio-economic%20reconstruction%20through%20democratic%20means.%20To%20achieve%20this%20purpose%20and%20to%20meet%20the%20special%20needs%20of%20India%2C%20the%20constitution%20framers%20developed%20a%20%3Cem%3Esui%20generis%3C%2Fem%3E%20variation%20of%20federation.%20The%20constitution%20incorporates%20federal%20features%20such%20as%20the%20distribution%20of%20powers%20between%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20States%3A%2097%20matters%20are%20on%20the%20Union%20List%3B%20States%20have%20exclusive%20powers%20on%2066%20matters%20contained%20in%20the%20State%20List%3B%20and%20the%20Concurrent%20List%20consists%20of%2047%20items.%20The%20constitution%20envisages%20India%E2%80%99s%20governance%20as%20a%20joint%20venture%20between%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments.%20But%20of%20late%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20launched%20an%20assault%20on%20the%20federal%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%20by%20attempting%20to%20capture%20areas%20and%20subjects%20which%20are%20within%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20states.%20This%20commandeering%20of%20civil%20services%20and%20the%20armed%20forces%20to%20trumpet%20the%20%E2%80%9Cachievements%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20the%20prime%20minister%20directly%20to%20the%20people%20would%20further%20worsen%20the%20situation%20and%20accelerate%20Centre-state%20tension%20and%20friction.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESecond%20is%20the%20code%20of%20conduct.%20Under%20Rule%205(1)%20of%20the%20Civil%20Services%20Conduct%20Rules%2C%201964%2C%20no%20government%20servant%20shall%20take%20part%20in%2C%20subscribe%20to%2C%20aid%20of%20or%20assist%20in%20any%20other%20manner%2C%20any%20political%20movement%20or%20activity.%20Engaging%20members%20of%20any%20of%20the%20central%20civil%20services%20in%20the%20Rath%20Prabhari%20campaign%2C%20which%20is%20clearly%20political%20in%20nature%2C%20would%20therefore%20infringe%20the%20Civil%20Services%20Conduct%20Rules.%20%E2%80%9CRath%20Prabhari%E2%80%9D%20itself%20is%20a%20political%20(mainly%20BJP)%20parlance%20and%20not%20that%20of%20civil%20service.%20Considering%20that%20the%20idea%20underlying%20this%20campaign%20exclusively%20revolves%20around%20the%20BJP%20government%E2%80%99s%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cachievements%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20past%20nine%20years%2C%20inevitably%2C%20it%20has%20a%20political%20connotation%20that%20cannot%20be%20wished%20away.%20Had%20the%20campaign%20covered%20the%20entire%20post-independence%20period%20as%20we%20celebrate%20the%20Diamond%20Jubilee%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20a%20different%20proposition.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcivil-servants-rath-prabharis-km-chandrasekhar-interview%5C%22%3EIt%20Is%20Not%20Civil%20Servants%E2%80%99%20Job%20to%20%E2%80%98Showcase%E2%80%99%20Govt%20Achievements%3A%20Former%20Cabinet%20Secretary%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20third%20dimension%20is%20the%20grave%20impropriety%20of%20it%20all.%20Civil%20servants%20and%20soldiers%20are%20not%20BJP%20cadres.%20Just%20as%20there%20is%20separation%20of%20powers%20between%20the%20judiciary%2C%20the%20executive%20and%20the%20legislature%20in%20the%20constitutional%20scheme%2C%20there%20is%20a%20clear%20line%20of%20separation%20between%20governments%20that%20come%20and%20go%20in%20a%20democracy%2C%20and%20the%20bureaucracy%2C%20which%20is%20permanent.%20The%20bureaucracy%E2%80%99s%20role%20is%20to%20conceive%2C%20design%2C%20plan%2C%20implement%20and%20supervise%20policies%20and%20programmes%20of%20a%20government.%20Its%20job%20is%20not%20to%20do%20propaganda%20for%20the%20same%2C%20since%20another%20government%20voted%20in%20by%20the%20people%20has%20the%20right%20to%20change%20the%20policies%20and%20programmes%20of%20one%20government.%20The%20%E2%80%98Rath%20Prabhari%E2%80%99%20programme%20envisaged%20by%20the%20present%20government%20is%20clearly%20a%20political%20programme%20intended%20to%20publicise%20its%20claimed%20achievements%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%20This%20amounts%20to%20misusing%20government%20machinery%20for%20election%20purposes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fourth%20dimension%20is%20the%20core%20electoral%20code%20of%20a%20level%20playing%20field%2C%20which%20is%20critical%20for%20the%20conduct%20of%20free%20and%20fair%20elections.%20The%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20has%20directed%20the%20government%20not%20to%20conduct%20the%20campaign%20in%20the%20states%20(Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Telangana%2C%20Chattisgarh%20and%20Mizoram)%20where%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20has%20come%20into%20effect%20due%20to%20assembly%20elections.%20Otherwise%2C%20the%20ECI%20has%20no%20problem%20with%20government%20servants%20openly%20participating%20in%20this%20political%20propaganda%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20parliament%20elections%20in%202024.%20This%20is%20a%20grave%20dereliction%20of%20duty%20by%20the%20ECI.%20The%20commission%20should%20have%20stopped%20this%20serious%20distortion%20of%20the%20electoral%20code%20and%20level%20playing%20field%20by%20invoking%20its%20plenipotentiary%20powers%20and%20the%20far-reaching%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1831036%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMohinder%20Singh%20Gill%20vs%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1978)%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20but%20where%20such%20law%20is%20silent%2C%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20Constitution%20is%20a%20reservoir%20of%20power%20to%20act%20for%20the%20avowed%20purpose%20of%20not%20divorced%20from%2C%20pushing%20forward%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20election%20with%20expedition%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20%E2%80%9Cfree%20and%20fair%20election%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoliticisation%20of%20armed%20forces%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20coming%20to%20the%20brazen%20politicisation%20of%20the%20armed%20forces%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98selfie%20points%E2%80%99%20that%20have%20already%20come%20up%20in%20some%20places.%20The%20SOP%20lays%20down%20the%20themes%20based%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20catchphrases%20including%20Atmanirbhar%20Bharat%2C%20Sashaktikaran%2C%20Nari%20Shakti%2C%20digitisation%20etc.%20Look%20at%20the%20tearing%20hurry%20of%20the%20MoD%20to%20execute%20the%20scheme.%20Directions%20were%20given%20on%20October%206%2C%20execution%20to%20commence%20%E2%80%9Cimmediately%E2%80%9D%20and%20action%20taken%20report%20to%20be%20submitted%20by%20October%2011.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIs%20it%20the%20execution%20of%20a%20routine%20scheme%20or%20%E2%80%98all-hands-on-deck%E2%80%99%20to%20identify%20national%20defence%2C%20particularly%20the%20armed%20forces%2C%20with%20the%20political%20party%20in%20power%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fopinion%2Ftiming-of-mods-modi-selfie-points-is-alarming-military-must-not-become-a-political-tool%2F1819305%2F%5C%22%3Easks%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20distinguished%20soldier%20Lt%20Gen%20H.S.%20Panag%20(Retd)!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20move%20by%20the%20government%20violates%20Rule%2020%20(1)%20of%20Army%20Rules%20(1954)%2C%20which%20says%20that%20no%20person%20subject%20to%20the%20Army%20Act%20shall%20take%20part%20in%20any%20activity%20held%20for%20political%20purposes.%20Also%2C%20the%20SOP%20suggesting%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98selfie%20points%E2%80%99%20may%20contain%20a%20giant-sized%20picture%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%20is%20questionable%20because%20as%20per%20Article%2053(2)%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20supreme%20command%20of%20the%20defence%20forces%20of%20the%20Union%20shall%20be%20vested%20in%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Republic%2C%20not%20the%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22121154%2F27368739091_b8ef73115b_k.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22121154%2F27368739091_b8ef73115b_k.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22121154%2F27368739091_b8ef73115b_k-300x148.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22121154%2F27368739091_b8ef73115b_k-1024x504.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-620691%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22591%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image%20of%20the%20Indian%20Army.%20Photo%3A%20Public.Resource.Org%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20former%20Chief%20of%20Naval%20Staff%20was%20emphatic%20when%20he%20said%20that%20this%20programme%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20never%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20contemplated%20and%20would%20have%20a%20negative%20long-term%20impact%20on%20the%20forces.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fopinion%2Ftiming-of-mods-modi-selfie-points-is-alarming-military-must-not-become-a-political-tool%2F1819305%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20not%20quite%20clear%20about%20the%20concept%20underpinning%20the%20%E2%80%9Cselfie%20points%E2%80%9D%20programme%2C%20but%20with%20the%20general%20election%20looming%2C%20any%20endeavour%20which%20even%20remotely%20involves%20the%20armed%20forces%20with%20political%20influencing%2C%20can%20only%20ring%20alarm%20bells.%20The%20MoD%20should%20never%20have%20contemplated%20this%2C%20and%20one%20hopes%20the%20military%20leadership%20will%20explain%20the%20deleterious%20long-term%20impact%20of%20politics%20on%20the%20morale%20%26amp%3B%20cohesion%20of%20our%20professional%20forces.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20else%20can%20one%20expect%20from%20a%20political%20dispensation%20hungry%20for%20power%2C%20and%20whose%20top%20leader%20in%202019%20described%20the%20Indian%20Army%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EModiji%20ki%20sena%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20ECI%20did%20not%20lift%20a%20small%20finger%2C%20despite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnavy-chief-yogi-adityanath-army-election-commission%5C%22%3Estrong%20protests%20by%20ex-servicemen%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20intriguing%20why%20the%20present%20ruling%20dispensation%20%E2%80%93%20with%20its%20massive%20propaganda%20machinery%20like%20a%20large%20political%20party%2C%20RSS%20and%20affiliate%20associations%2C%20IT%20Cell%20and%20a%20pliant%20media%20%E2%80%93%20should%20commandeer%20the%20civil%20services%20and%20the%20armed%20forces%20for%20the%20purpose.%20A%20question%20arises%3A%20Is%20there%20a%20credibility%20crisis%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBe%20that%20as%20it%20may%2C%20we%20call%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20gained%20independence%20one%20day%20before%20us%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfailed%20state%E2%80%9D%20mainly%20because%20of%20its%20hijacking%20of%20the%20civil%20services%20and%20politicisation%20of%20the%20armed%20forces.%20Is%20India%20heading%20that%20way%3F%20As%20it%20is%20because%20of%20the%20brazen%20crony%20capitalism%20the%20country%20resembles%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfailed%20state%E2%80%9D%20as%20defined%20by%20Robert%20Rothberg%20in%20the%20seminal%20book%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2Fj.ctt7scrg%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWhen%20States%20Fail%3A%20Causes%20and%20Consequences%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CFailed%20states%20offer%20unparalleled%20economic%20opportunity-but%20only%20for%20a%20privileged%20few.%20Those%20around%20the%20ruler%20or%20ruling%20oligarchy%20grow%20richer%20while%20their%20less%20fortunate%20brethren%20starve%E2%80%A6%20The%20privilege%20of%20making%20real%20money%20when%20everything%20else%20is%20deteriorating%20is%20confined%20to%20clients%20of%20the%20ruling%20elite%E2%80%A6%20The%20nation-state%E2%80%99s%20responsibility%20to%20maximize%20the%20well-being%20and%20prosperity%20of%20all%20its%20citizens%20is%20conspicuously%20absent%2C%20if%20it%20ever%20existed%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECommandeering%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20civil%20services%20and%20the%20armed%20forces%20for%20political%20propaganda%2C%20thereby%20severely%20denting%20their%20independence%20and%20integrity%2C%20will%20only%20hasten%20the%20process.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fm-g-devasahayam-2%5C%22%3EM.G.%20Devasahayam%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20former%20Army%20and%20IAS%20officer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699010965000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25154708%2FScreenshot-2023-10-25-at-3.46.47-PM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcivil-services-armed-forces-propaganda-india-failed-state%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20'Rath%20Prabhari'%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence's%20'selfie-point'%20orders%20are%20obviously%20aimed%20at%20creating%20a%20positive%20public%20perception%20of%20the%20BJP%20government%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20general%20elections%20in%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcivil-services-armed-forces-propaganda-india-failed-state%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Loss%20of%20International%20Support%20Looms%20Over%20Israel%20as%20Gaza%20Death%20Toll%20Climbs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25123525%2FF9O1QYgbQAARmyY.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20past%20four%20decades%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20experience%20of%20fighting%20paramilitary%20militias%20has%20been%20grim.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIts%20last%20major%20operation%20was%20in%20southern%20Lebanon%2C%20which%20started%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adl.org%2Fresources%2Fbackgrounder%2Flebanon-war-1982%5C%22%3EOperation%20Peace%20for%20Galilee%20in%201982%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20initially%20successful%2C%20the%20subsequent%20occupation%20of%20southern%20Lebanon%20led%20directly%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Hezbollah%20Shia%20militias%2C%20persistent%20losses%20for%20the%20Israel%20Defence%20Forces%20(IDF)%2C%20a%20withdrawal%20to%20a%20nine-mile%20security%20zone%20within%20three%20years%20and%20from%20Lebanon%20as%20a%20whole%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202006%20Israeli%20military%20units%20went%20back%20into%20Lebanon%20to%20counter%20Hezbollah%20rockets%20but%20ended%20with%20exhausted%20troops%20withdrawing%20in%20some%20disarray%20and%20the%20IDF%20resorting%20to%20a%20massive%20air%20war%20that%20did%20huge%20damage%20to%20the%20infrastructure%20of%20much%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20current%20war%2C%20the%20IDF%20fought%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2022%2F8%2F7%2Ftimeline-israels-attacks-on-gaza-since-2005%5C%22%3Efour%20other%20wars%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202007%2C%20primarily%20to%20control%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20rockets%20and%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F28%2Fa-spiders-web-of-tunnels-inside-gazas-underground-network-being-targeted-by-israel%5C%22%3Egrowing%20network%20of%20infiltration%20tunnels%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20most%20significant%20one%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasebook.icrc.org%2Fcase-study%2Fisraelpalestine-operation-protective-edge-gaza-13-june-26-august-2014%5C%22%3EOperation%20Protective%20Edge%20in%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20involved%20troops%20in%20a%20ground%20assault.%20In%20the%20event%2C%20they%20found%20the%20fighting%20extremely%20difficult%2C%20with%20the%20elite%20Golani%20Brigade%20experiencing%20serious%20casualties%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOnce%20again%2C%20there%20was%20intense%20use%20of%20air%20power%20and%2C%20as%20in%20the%20other%20wars%2C%20it%20was%20civilians%20that%20suffered%20most.%20Overall%2C%20the%20Israelis%20lost%20more%20than%20300%20killed%20in%20those%20four%20wars%20but%20for%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2023%2Foct%2F25%2Fisrael-hamas-war-assault-gaza-doomed-to-failure%5C%22%3Edeath%20toll%20exceeded%205%2C300%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBitter%20experience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExperiences%20in%20other%20wars%20are%20relevant%20to%20what%20happens%20now%20in%20Gaza.%20After%20the%209%2F11%20attacks%20there%20was%20considerable%20international%20support%20for%20the%20US.%20War%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opendemocracy.net%2Fen%2Fafghanistan_3849jsp%2F%5C%22%3Eagainst%20the%20Taliban%20seemed%3C%2Fa%3E%20inevitable%20though%20very%20few%20security%20analysts%20warned%20of%20the%20US-led%20coalition%20falling%20into%20a%20trap.%20The%20warnings%20were%20ignored%20and%2020%20years%20later%20the%20western%20troops%20finally%20retreated%20in%20disarray.%20Then%20came%20the%20Iraq%20war%20from%202003%2C%20with%20warnings%20once%20again%20ignored%20and%2C%20once%20again%2C%20with%20disastrous%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20to%20Gaza%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20concerns%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opendemocracy.net%2Fen%2Fafghanistan_3849jsp%2F%5C%22%3Ewhat%20comes%20next%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20current%20incursions%20being%20far%20short%20of%20a%20full-scale%20ground%20intervention.%20There%20are%20sharp%20differences%20of%20belief%20of%20what%20should%20come%20next%20within%20the%20military%20and%20within%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20government%20as%20well%20as%20within%20Israel%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20with%20much%20of%20it%20heightened%20by%20the%20concern%20over%20the%20loss%20of%20international%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20concern%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F24%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fisrael-hamas-invasion.html%5C%22%3Eexperience%20of%20urban%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%20elsewhere.%20Just%20six%20years%20ago%2C%20it%20took%20nine%20months%20for%20the%20US-led%20coalition%20to%20take%20back%20the%20Iraqi%20city%20of%20Mosul%20from%20Islamic%20State.%20The%20US%20led%20the%20huge%20air%20assault%2C%20aided%20by%20France%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20other%20partners.%20The%20ground%20forces%20then%20were%20Iraqi%20troops%20and%20militias%20and%20they%20lost%208%2C200%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20further%2010%2C000%20civilians%20were%20killed%2C%20and%20the%20old%20city%20was%20wrecked.%20It%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iwm.org.uk%2Fhistory%2Fwhat-you-need-to-know-about-the-battle-of-stalingrad%5C%22%3Elikened%20to%20Stalingrad%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20early%201943.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJust%20last%20year%2C%20a%20small%20force%20of%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20held%20off%20a%20large%20Russian%20force%20for%20nearly%20three%20months%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F07%2F24%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraine-war-mariupol-azovstal.html%5C%22%3Esiege%20of%20the%20Azovstal%20steel%20works%20in%20Mariupol%3C%2Fa%3E%20using%20a%20network%20of%2024%20kilometres%20of%20Soviet-era%20tunnels.%20Hamas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F28%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fgazas-tunnels-israel-ground-war.html%5C%22%3Ehas%20constructed%20vastly%20more%20tunnels%20under%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20no%20doubt%20ready%20for%20months%20of%20combat.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThree%20weeks%20ago%2C%20Israel%20suffered%20a%20grievous%20loss%20and%20rightly%20got%20huge%20initial%20support%2C%20but%20that%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F29%2Fuae-calls-emergency-un-security-council-meeting-to-seek-pause-to-gaza-fighting%5C%22%3Ealready%20fading%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Worse%20still%2C%20there%20is%20a%20terrible%20inability%20of%20the%20current%20Israeli%20government%20to%20understand%20what%20it%20is%20dealing%20with%20in%20a%20ground%20invasion%20of%20Gaza.%20But%20the%20death%20toll%20tells%20us%20all%20we%20need%20to%20know.%20If%20we%20look%20at%20the%20five%20Gaza%20wars%20since%202007%2C%20including%20the%20current%20devastating%20war%2C%20the%20Israelis%20have%20lost%201%2C700%20people%2C%20but%20the%20Palestinians%20have%20lost%20more%20than%2013%2C000%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20numbers%20are%20rising%20by%20hundreds%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20public%20mood%20in%20Israel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F29%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fisrael-reservists-hamas-war.html%5C%22%3Estill%20supports%20the%20Netanyahu%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20however%20unpopular%20it%20might%20have%20been%20just%20a%20month%20ago.%20But%20the%20small%20but%20persistent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Ffamilies-israeli-hostages-taken-by-hamas-tour-europe-keep-focus-plight-2023-10-26%2F%5C%22%3Ecampaign%20by%20families%20of%20the%20hostages%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20them%20to%20be%20the%20priority%20is%20having%20an%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%2C%20it%20is%20the%20change%20of%20mood%20internationally%20that%20is%20a%20deep%20concern%20in%20Israel%20and%2C%20indeed%2C%20in%20the%20Biden%20administration.%20This%20was%20shown%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fun-resolution-vote-israel-hamas-gaza-truce-7eec00b0e28ef2036636b166b48ca030%5C%22%3Eweekend%20debate%20in%20the%20UN%20general%20assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20only%2012%20states%20supported%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20in%20voting%20against%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20pause%E2%80%9D.%20Also%2C%20eight%20EU%20states%20were%20among%20the%20120%20supporting%20the%20motion%20and%20the%2045%20who%20abstained%20even%20included%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20previous%20Israeli%20military%20actions%2C%20the%20end%20has%20effectively%20come%20about%20when%20international%20support%20for%20Israel%20has%20collapsed%20or%20got%20close%20to%20that.%20If%20the%20ground%20war%20against%20Hamas%20had%20started%20within%20a%20few%20days%20of%20the%20shock%20of%20October%207%2C%20and%20if%20that%20operation%20had%20been%20successful%20and%20Hamas%20had%20collapsed%2C%20then%20Netanyahu%20could%20have%20claimed%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThat%20has%20not%20happened%20and%20will%20not%20happen%20now.%20Instead%2C%20there%20is%20every%20prospect%20of%20a%20bitter%20war%20with%20many%20thousands%20more%20Palestinians%20killed%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20young%20Palestinians%20all%20too%20ready%20to%20fight%20in%20the%20future%2C%20and%20a%20peaceful%20resolution%20of%20the%20Israel%2FPalestine%20conflict%20delayed%20by%20at%20least%20another%20generation.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F216582%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fpaul-rogers-112929%5C%22%3EPaul%20Rogers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Peace%20Studies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-bradford-911%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Bradford%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%2