and%20one%20is%20free%20to%20take%20sides%2C%20her%20statement%20of%20having%20been%20disrobed%20(albeit%20figuratively)%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fmahua-moitra-cheerharan-ethics-panel-meeting-sonkar-cash-for-query-2457316-2023-11-02%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Evastraharan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20by%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliamentary-ethics-committee-opposition-mps-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edogged%20line%20of%20questioning%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20by%20the%20committee%20chairperson%2C%20meant%20to%20outrage%20her%20modesty%2C%20raises%20some%20serious%20questions%20and%20gives%20us%20much%20to%20reflect%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmahua-moitra-ramesh-bidhuri-very-different-parliament-committee%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Very%20Different%20Approach%20for%20BJP%20MP%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri%E2%80%99%3A%20Mahua%20Moitra%20Writes%20to%20Parliament%20Committee%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20one%2C%20drawing%20a%20parallel%20between%20Draupadi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echeerharan%2Fvastraharan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20(disrobing)%20may%20sound%20like%20an%20excellent%20analogy%20%E2%80%93%20while%20being%20a%20deliberate%20nudge%20to%20potential%20news%20headlines%20%E2%80%93%20suggestive%20also%20of%20the%20sharpening%20divide%20between%20us%20versus%20them%2C%20before%20the%20upcoming%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20there%20is%20more%20to%20it%20than%20meets%20the%20eye.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20changed%20since%20%3Cem%3EMahabharat%3C%2Fem%3E%20days%2C%20remarkably%20and%20concerningly%2C%20is%20the%20solitude%20of%20the%20woman%20in%20frame.%20While%20there%20was%20one%20Draupadi%20who%20garnered%20all%20the%20attention%20with%20other%20female%20characters%20essentially%20staying%20on%20the%20fringes%20as%20the%20Mahabharat%20unfolded%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20very%20different%20now%20%E2%80%93%20with%20Moitra%20doing%20all%20the%20batting%20and%20the%20fielding%20seemingly%20%E2%80%98alone%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20some%20are%20calling%20her%20the%20%E2%80%98bengal%20tigress%E2%80%99%2C%20what%20lies%20hidden%20in%20the%20analogy%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20tigers%2C%20especially%20bengal%20tigers%2C%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalgeographic.com%2Fanimals%2Fmammals%2Ffacts%2Fbengal-tiger%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eknown%20to%20live%20alone%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20So%20while%20TMC%20or%20other%20official%20parties%20haven%E2%80%99t%20come%20out%20openly%20in%20her%20support%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20for%20women%20all%20across%20India%20to%20show%20that%20today%E2%80%99s%20Draupadi%20will%20not%20stand%20alone.%20That%20she%20will%20have%20the%20support%20of%20sisterhood%20and%20even%20brotherhood%20pouring%20in%20for%20her%2C%20across%20party%20lines%20and%20ideally%20across%20ideology%20lines%2C%20for%20isn%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%98respect%20for%20women%E2%80%99%20the%20tagline%20of%20most%20political%20parties%20in%20one%20form%20or%20the%20other%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAsking%20an%20MP%20about%20%E2%80%98who%20she%20calls%20late%20in%20the%20night%3F%E2%80%99%20or%20making%20innuendos%20about%20her%20character%20in%20an%20ethics%20committee%20discussion%20is%20absolutely%20abominable%20and%20cannot%20be%20allowed%20to%20stand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20women%20playing%20a%20victim%20card%2C%20but%20simply%20a%20chance%20to%20address%20the%20elephant%20in%20the%20room%20and%20not%20just%20the%20tigress%20(pun%20intended).%20Women%20in%20politics%20in%20India%20have%20long%20been%20beaten%20with%20a%20characteristic%20%E2%80%98toolkit%E2%80%99%2C%20one%20that%20involves%20questioning%20their%20character%2C%20never%20their%20policies%3B%20branding%20her%20as%20too%20loud%20or%20aggressive%20or%20ambitious%3B%20questioning%20the%20personal%20choices%20she%20makes%20(what%20she%20wears%2C%20or%20who%20she%20dates%20etc.).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliamentary-ethics-committee-opposition-mps-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3EMahua%20Moitra%20Slams%20Ethics%20Committee%20Probe%20as%20%E2%80%98Filthy%2C%20Unethical%E2%80%99%2C%20Finds%20Support%20From%20Opposition%20MPs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20have%20got%20to%20say%20enough!%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20it%20should%20be%20said%20loud%20and%20clear%20by%20women%20%E2%80%93%20all%20women%2C%20who%20care%2C%20not%20just%20TMC%20women%20but%20also%20Congress%20women%20and%20BJP%20women%20and%20non-political%20or%20apolitical%20women.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20in%20India%20need%20to%20proclaim%20that%20we%20cannot%20let%20women%20be%20taken%20down%20by%20shutting%20us%20up%20with%20a%20handbook%20that%20should%20ideally%20be%20a%20remnant%20of%20the%20past.%20We%20need%20to%20announce%20our%20own%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Manifesto%2C%20which%20needs%20to%20be%20hung%20on%20every%20door%2C%20every%20office%20wall%2C%20every%20twitter%20account%20and%20it%20can%20go%20like%20this.%20Repeat%20after%20me%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Col%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20be%20as%20bold%2C%20aggressive%20and%20ambitious%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20choose%20to%20be%20or%20not%20to%20be%20%E2%80%93%20someone%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20girlfriend%2C%20friend%3B%20fashionable%20or%20not%3B%20wear%20make%20up%20or%20not%3B%20be%20single%20or%20not%3B%20work%20or%20not%3B%20have%20babies%20or%20not%20%3B%20wear%20hijab%20or%20not%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20stay%20out%20late%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20for%20parties%20or%20for%20meetings%20or%20with%20friends%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20question%20%E2%80%93%20societal%20norms%2C%20governance%20policies%2C%20financial%20decisions%20(including%20Adani)%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20do%20all%20things%20otherwise%20legal%20for%20men%20%E2%80%93%20to%20pray%2C%20to%20follow%20their%20beliefs%2C%20to%20smoke%20or%20drink%20or%20break%20taboos%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20sit%20cross-legged%20or%20not%2C%20wear%20jeans%20or%20skirts%2C%20take%20last%20names%20or%20not%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20ask%20for%20a%20rise%20in%20pay%2C%20a%20rise%20in%20position%2C%20a%20share%20in%20property%2C%20for%20what%E2%80%99s%20their%20due%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20do%20nothing%2C%20and%20stand%20aimlessly%20on%20roads%2C%20in%20parks%2C%20outside%20homes%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20the%20right%20to%20be%20noisy%2C%20to%20cry%20or%20laugh%2C%20to%20shout%20or%20to%20be%20silent%2C%20to%20have%20their%20privacy%20respected%20and%20do%20whatever%20they%20want%20in%20their%20private%20time%2C%20just%20as%20men%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%20have%20a%20right%20to%20call%20out%20bullshit%2C%20wherever%20they%20see%20it%2C%20just%20like%20men%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Fol%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20while%20calling%20for%20immediate%20implementation%20of%20the%20Women%20Reservation%20Act%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fpriyankagandhi%2Fstatus%2F1713509000447479917%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPriyanka%20Gandhi%20asked%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20why%20women%20are%20still%20slaves%2C%20and%20made%20a%20passionate%20appeal%20that%20we%20have%20to%20see%20ourselves%20beyond%20the%20repressive%20system%20that%20has%20been%20pressed%20upon%20us%20for%20generations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20cannot%20see%20more%20women%20be%20hanged%20by%20public%20opinion%2C%20through%20a%20distorted%2C%20vilified%2C%20systemic%20attack%20on%20them.%20Also%2C%20the%20time%20for%20mere%20tokenism%20on%20women%20issues%20is%20over.%20We%20have%20to%20let%20it%20be%20known%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.poetryfoundation.org%2Fpoems%2F46446%2Fstill-i-rise%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMaya%20Angelou%E2%80%99s%20inspiring%20words%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethat%20we%20will%20rise%2C%20and%20that%20we%20shall%20rise%20together.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20power%20to%20Mahua%20Moitra.%20Know%20that%20you%20are%20not%20alone!%20And%20for%20those%20of%20you%20reading%2C%20speak%20up.%20For%20today%20it%E2%80%99s%20her%2C%20tomorrow%20it%20will%20be%20one%20of%20us.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EAvani%20Bansal%20is%20a%20lawyer%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Congress%20party.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699005630000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F06%2F10183720%2FKT-Mahua-Moitra-10-June-2021.00_31_44_16.Still004.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Ftodays-draupadi-will-not-stand-alone%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Women%20in%20politics%20in%20India%20have%20long%20been%20beaten%20with%20a%20characteristic%20%E2%80%98toolkit%E2%80%99%2C%20one%20that%20involves%20questioning%20their%20character.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A79%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Ftodays-draupadi-will-not-stand-alone%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kalakshetra%3A%20Revathi%20Ramachandran%20Steps%20Down%20as%20Director%2C%20Aneish%20Rajan%20Takes%20Charge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03135327%2FF96u2jba4AALEnM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20after%20allegations%20of%20sexual%20harassment%20and%20abuse%20surfaced%20at%20Chennai%E2%80%99s%20Kalakshetra%20Foundation%2C%20director%20Revathi%20Ramachandran%20has%20stepped%20down%20from%20office.%20She%20will%20be%20replaced%20by%20Aneish%20Rajan%2C%20deputy%20secretary%20at%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Culture.%C2%A0%20Kalakshetra%20announced%20the%20transfer%20of%20power%20on%20Thursday%2C%20November%202%20on%20their%20social%20media%20handles.%20Sources%20in%20Kalakshetra%20told%20%3Cem%3ETNM%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Aneish%20was%20taking%20over%20only%20as%20an%20acting%20director%2C%20but%20this%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20change%20of%20directors%20comes%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20allegations%20of%20harassment%20at%20the%20Rukmini%20Devi%20College%20of%20Fine%20Arts%20(RDFCA)%2C%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Kalakshetra%20Foundation.%20Though%20the%20allegations%20surfaced%20in%20December%20of%20last%20year%2C%20students%20battled%20with%20the%20administration%20for%20months%20before%20their%20complaints%20were%20taken%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAn%20inquiry%20committee%20helmed%20by%20retired%20judge%20Justice%20K.%20Kannan%2C%20and%20comprising%20of%20former%20Tamil%20Nadu%20director%20general%20of%20police%20(DGP)%20Letika%20Saran%20and%20Shobha%20Varthaman%2C%20set%20up%20by%20S.%20Ramadorai%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20Kalakshetra%20Foundation%20in%20April%202023%2C%20recommended%20that%20able%20administrators%20with%20%E2%80%9Cbackground%20in%20human%20resources%20management%20and%20organisational%20skills%2C%20with%20a%20high%20level%20of%20interest%20in%20performing%20arts%20as%20additional%20interest%2C%20shall%20alone%20be%20considered%20for%20the%20posts%20of%20the%20chief%20functionaries%2C%20such%20as%20Director%20and%20Principal%20of%20the%20Institution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3ESmt.%20Revathi%20Ramachandran%20has%20demitted%20the%20charge%20of%20Director%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkalakshetrafdn%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40kalakshetrafdn%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20October%2031%2C%202023.%20Shri%20Aneish%20Rajan%2C%20has%20taken%20over%20as%20Director%20(IC)%20from%20November%2001%2C%202023%2C%20with%20Kalakshetra%20Foundation%E2%80%99s%20Governing%20Board%20members%20and%20Advisor%20present%20during%20the%20occasion.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FioXCT9Jml5%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FioXCT9Jml5%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Kalakshetra%20India%20(%40kalakshetrafdn)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fkalakshetrafdn%2Fstatus%2F1720004710458171839%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%202%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EAniesh%20Rajan%20is%20a%20former%20Revenue%20Service%20Officer%20(IRS)%20who%20had%20previously%20served%20as%20the%20Kerala%20Customs%20Department%20Joint%20Commissioner%20before%20he%20became%20deputy%20secretary%20in%202022.%20His%20service%20as%20the%20joint%20commissioner%20was%20marred%20at%20the%20time%20by%20accusations%20of%20a%20political%20nature%20during%20the%20high-profile%20Thiruvananthapuram%20gold%20smuggling%20case%2C%20and%20Aneish%20was%20then%20transferred%20from%20Kochi%20to%20Nagpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20protests%20in%20Kalakshetra%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStudents%20of%20RDFCA%20had%20come%20forward%20with%20sexual%20harassment%20allegations%20against%20senior%20faculty%20Hari%20Padman%20and%20three%20members%20of%20the%20repertory%20%E2%80%94%20Sanjith%20Lal%2C%20Sai%20Krishnan%2C%20and%20Srinath.%20Following%20this%2C%20on%20March%2031%2C%20they%20staged%20a%20night-long%20protest%20demanding%20action%20against%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EHari%20Padman%20was%20finally%20arrested%20on%20April%203%20after%20an%20FIR%20was%20lodged%20against%20him%20at%20the%20Adyar%20All%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Police%20Station%20(AWPS).%20He%20was%20released%20on%20bail%20in%20June.%20Meanwhile%2C%20no%20legal%20action%20has%20been%20taken%20so%20far%20against%20the%20other%20three%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20course%20of%20the%20student%20and%20public%20outcry%2C%20two%20survivors%20and%20six%20staff%20members%20spoke%20to%20%3Cem%3ETNM%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20March%202023%2C%20detailing%20how%20the%20atmosphere%20at%20the%20Kalakshetra%20campus%20was%20toxic.%20The%20survivors%20told%20%3Cem%3ETNM%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Hari%20Padman%20would%20invite%20them%20to%20his%20residence%20within%20the%20campus%2C%20and%20denying%20his%20advances%20invited%20severe%20humiliation%20and%20repercussions%2C%20even%20leading%20to%20some%20women%20quitting%20their%20course%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStudents%20had%20also%20told%20TNM%20that%20their%20appeals%20for%20justice%20to%20Revathi%20Ramachandran%20had%20been%20dismissed%20outright%20or%20not%20given%20due%20importance.%20Moreover%2C%20students%20and%20faculty%20members%20have%20also%20said%20that%20the%20atmosphere%20on%20campus%20was%20casteist%20and%20misogynistic%20with%20women%20students%20constantly%20under%20the%20scanner.%20It%20also%20came%20to%20light%20that%20Revathi%20had%20allegedly%20covered%20up%20a%20mass%20outbreak%20of%20food%20poisoning%20on%20campus%20from%20the%20hostel%20food%20in%202021%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20When%20students%20became%20vocal%20about%20the%20attempted%20cover-up%2C%20they%20allegedly%20faced%20more%20retaliation%20from%20Revathi%20who%20accused%20them%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpainting%20her%20in%20a%20bad%20light.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20April%20this%20year%2C%20a%20transwoman%20alumna%20of%20the%20RDCFA%20wrote%20to%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20State%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Commission%20(SWC)%20%3Cins%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftamil-nadu%2Fkalakshetra-alumna-alleges-sexual-assault-governing-board-member-writes-swc-176341%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elodging%20a%20complaint%20of%20sexual%20assault%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fins%3Eand%20transphobia%20against%20several%20Kalakshetra%20employees%20including%20current%20governing%20board%20member%20P.T.%20Narendran.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20inquiry%20committee%20found%20Hari%20Padman%20guilty%20of%20gross%20misconduct%20and%20suggested%20that%20the%20students%20who%20complained%20of%20sexual%20misbehaviour%20by%20Sanjith%20Lal%2C%20Saikrishna%2C%20and%20Srinath%2C%20be%20provided%20with%20legal%20assistance%20to%20file%20police%20complaints.%20The%20report%20further%20says%20that%20any%20sexual%20intent%20of%20the%20teacher%20to%20a%20student%20is%20an%20abhorrent%20expression%20of%20asymmetry%20of%20power.%20It%20also%20recommended%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20students%E2%80%99%20grievances%20redressal%20committee%2C%20as%20contemplated%20by%20the%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20(UGC)%20Regulations%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20contents%20of%20the%20report%2C%20which%20was%20written%20many%20months%20ago%2C%20remain%20unpublished%20to%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftamil-nadu%2Frevathi-ramachandran-steps-down-as-director-of-kalakshetra-aneish-rajan-takes-charge%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20by%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20News%20Minute%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699003773000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F03135327%2FF96u2jba4AALEnM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fkalakshetra-revathi-ramachandran-director-aneish-rajan%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20change%20comes%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20allegations%20of%20harassment%20at%20the%20Rukmini%20Devi%20College%20of%20Fine%20Arts%2C%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Kalakshetra%20Foundation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fkalakshetra-revathi-ramachandran-director-aneish-rajan%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Real%20Mystery%20of%20the%20Manish%20Sisodia%20Case%20Is%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20About-Face%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%204%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20led%20by%20Justice%20Sanjeev%20Khanna%2C%20hearing%20former%20Delhi%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20and%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20leader%20Manish%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20bail%20plea%20in%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-money-has-come-to-manish-sisodia-how-will-you-bring-him-under-pmla-sc-to-ed%5C%22%3Easked%20the%20ED%20if%20it%20had%20any%20proof%3C%2Fa%3E%20other%20than%20the%20statement%20of%20a%20co-accused%20who%20had%20turned%20approver%20against%20Sisodia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20CBI%20arrested%20Sisodia%20on%20February%2026%2C%20charging%20him%20with%20taking%20a%20bribe%20for%20tweaking%20the%20excise%20policy%20of%20the%20Delhi%20government%20to%20favour%20a%20liquor%20lobby.%20On%20March%208%2C%20the%20ED%20formally%20charged%20Sisodia%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA).%20Since%20then%2C%20Sisodia%20has%20been%20in%20prison.%20From%20the%20lower%20courts%20up%20to%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20been%20denied%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Khanna%2C%20presiding%20over%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20which%20included%20Justice%20S.V.N.%20Bhatti%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20as%20per%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20the%20recipient%20of%20the%20proceeds%20of%20the%20crime%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20political%20party%E2%80%9D%20and%20not%20Sisodia%2C%20and%20asked%20why%20the%20party%20was%20not%20made%20an%20accused.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20far%20as%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20(PMLA)%20is%20concerned%2C%20your%20whole%20case%20is%20that%20it%20went%20to%20a%20political%20party.%20That%20political%20party%20is%20still%20not%20an%20accused.%20How%20do%20you%20answer%20that%3F%20He%20is%20not%20the%20beneficiary%2C%20the%20political%20party%20is%20the%20beneficiary%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Khanna%20had%20stated%20then.%20On%20October%2017%2C%20repeating%20the%20same%20line%2C%20after%20arguments%20were%20concluded%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20announced%20that%20the%20verdict%20on%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20plea%20would%20be%20delivered%20on%20October%2030.%C2%A0%20Following%20this%2C%20the%20ED%20told%20the%20media%20that%20it%20was%20contemplating%20making%20AAP%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2030%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20wrote%20the%20verdict%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-manish-sisodia-bail%5C%22%3Erejecting%20Manish%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20bail%20plea%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20raising%20%E2%80%9Csome%20doubts%E2%80%9D%20about%20some%20of%20the%20charges%20levelled%20by%20the%20ED.%20He%20refrained%20%E2%80%9Cfrom%20delving%E2%80%A6%20in%20depth%20and%20detail%20into%20some%20of%20the%20legal%20questions%20arising%20in%20the%20matter%20and%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CHowever%20there%20is%20one%20clear%20ground%20or%20charge%20in%20the%20complaint%20filed%20under%20the%20PMLA%20which%20is%20free%20from%20perceptible%20legal%20challenge%20and%20the%20facts%20as%20alleged%20are%20tentatively%20supported%20by%20material%20evidence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20arguments%20Justice%20Khanna%2C%20leading%20the%20bench%2C%20had%20warned%20that%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20claims%20against%20Sisodia%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20fall%20flat%E2%80%9D%20after%20%E2%80%9Ctwo%20questions%20in%20the%20cross-examination.%E2%80%9D%20The%20ED%20had%20contended%20that%20the%20CBI%20investigating%20the%20alleged%20act%20of%20corruption%20had%20claimed%20that%20an%20amount%20of%20Rs%202.2%20crore%20was%20paid%20by%20Amit%20Arora%20through%20middleman%20Dinesh%20Arora.%20The%20bench%20pointed%20out%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Cis%20not%20a%20charge%20or%20an%20allegation%20made%20in%20the%20chargesheet%20filed%20by%20the%20CBI%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cit%20may%20be%20difficult%20to%20regard%20alleged%20payment%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cproceed%20of%20crime%20under%20the%20PMLA.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ED%20had%20claimed%20that%20part%20of%20the%20proceeds%20of%20the%20crime%20were%20used%20to%20fund%20the%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20poll%20campaign%20in%20Goa.%20However%2C%20the%20bench%20noted%20that%20the%20agency%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Conce%20the%20quantum%20of%20amount%20used%20in%20the%20election%20in%20Goa%20is%20ascertained%2C%20a%20decision%20to%20consider%20AAP%20as%20an%20accused%20under%20Section%203%20of%20the%20PMLA%20will%20be%20taken.%E2%80%9D%20Goa%20Assembly%20elections%20were%20held%20in%20February%2C%202022.%20But%20it%20is%20evident%20from%20whatever%20the%20ED%20stated%20in%20the%20apex%20court%20that%20after%20more%20than%2020%20months%20the%20ED%20has%20no%20idea%20how%20much%20the%20AAP%20spent%20on%20the%20Goa%20Assembly%20elections.%20And%20so%20there%20is%20no%20substance%20in%20its%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20charge%20that%E2%80%A6Sisodia%20is%20vicariously%20liable%20in%20terms%20of%20Section%2070%20of%20the%20PMLA%20cannot%20be%20alleged%20and%20has%20not%20been%20argued.%E2%80%9D%20The%20bench%20mentioned%20that%20%E2%80%9Cprima%20facie%20there%20is%20lack%20of%20clarity%2C%20as%20specific%20allegation%20on%20the%20involvement%20of%20%E2%80%A6Sisodia%2C%20direct%20or%20indirect%2C%20in%20the%20transfer%20of%20Rs%2045%20crore%20to%20AAP%20for%20Goa%20elections%20is%20missing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20noted%20that%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20that%20kickback%20of%20Rs%20100%20crore%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20actually%20paid%20by%20the%20liquor%20group%20is%20somewhat%20a%20matter%20of%20debate%2C%20questioning%20also%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20contention%E2%80%A6%20that%20generation%20of%20proceeds%20of%20crime%20is%20itself%20possession%20or%20use%20of%20the%20proceeds%20of%20crime.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20questions%20the%20bench%20raised%20and%20observations%20it%20made%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20arguments%20clearly%20demonstrated%20that%20it%20found%20no%20substance%20or%20strength%20in%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20case%20against%20Sisodia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESisodia%20has%20been%20in%20jail%20for%20the%20last%20eight%20months%2C%20despite%20the%20bench%20finding%20a%20very%20untenable%20case%20against%20the%20AAP%20leader.%20But%20on%20October%2030%2C%20when%20Justice%20Khanna%20delivered%20the%20judgement%2C%20it%20went%20totally%20against%20the%20kernel%20of%20his%20observations%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20arguments%20the%20ED%20had%20extended%20on%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20bail%20plea.%20That%20is%20the%20mysterious%20aspect%20of%20this%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20view%20of%20the%20aforesaid%20discussion%20and%20for%20the%20reasons%20stated%2C%20we%20are%20not%20inclined%20to%20accept%20the%20prayer%20for%20grant%20of%20bail%20at%20this%20stage.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20perhaps%20to%20assuage%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20hurt%20in%20denial%20of%20bail%2C%20it%20added%20that%20the%20prosecution%20had%20assured%20that%20the%20trial%20would%20be%20completed%20in%20six%20to%20eight%20months%20and%20added%20that%20Sisodia%20could%20file%20a%20fresh%20bail%20application%20if%20the%20trial%20was%20protracted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20effect%2C%20the%20bench%20ensured%20that%20Sisodia%20is%20not%20let%20out%20on%20bail%20before%20completing%20at%20least%20a%20year%20behind%20bars%2C%20without%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20happened%20between%20October%2017%20and%20October%2030%20that%20despite%20all%20the%20pertinent%20points%20Justice%20Khanna%20had%20made%20against%20the%20ED%20arguments%2C%20he%20suddenly%20found%20merit%20in%20the%20ED%20case%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20mystery%20that%20should%20engage%20everyone%E2%80%99s%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFaraz%20Ahmad%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20based%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699001754000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmanish-sisodia-supreme-court-bail-justice-khanna%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20happened%20between%20October%2017%20and%20October%2030%20that%20despite%20all%20the%20pertinent%20points%20Justice%20Khanna%20had%20made%20against%20the%20ED%20arguments%2C%20he%20suddenly%20found%20merit%20in%20the%20ED%20case%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmanish-sisodia-supreme-court-bail-justice-khanna%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Oct%207%20Hamas%20Attack%20'Big%20Act%20of%20Terrorism'%20But%20Need%20'Solution'%20to%20Palestinians'%20Problems%3A%20Jaishankar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30123119%2FUntitled-design-4-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20has%20asserted%20that%20a%20solution%20to%20the%20Palestine%20dispute%20has%20to%20be%20found%20and%20international%20humanitarian%20law%20has%20to%20be%20respected%2C%20while%20reiterating%20that%20the%20Hamas%20incursion%20into%20Israel%20on%20October%207%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbig%20act%20of%20terrorism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20at%20the%20joint%20session%20of%20the%20Joint%20Secretary%20Session%20of%20the%20Senate%E2%80%99s%20External%20Affairs%20and%20Defence%20Commission%20in%20Rome%2C%20Italy%2C%20on%20Thursday%2C%20November%202%2C%20external%20affairs%20minister%20S.%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20while%20terrorism%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunacceptable%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20solution%20had%20to%20be%20also%20found%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cproblems%20faced%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20people%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20initial%20reaction%20to%20October%207%20%E2%80%93%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%E2%80%93%20had%20only%20been%20to%20express%20%E2%80%9Csolidarity%20with%20Israel%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20Modi%20then%20reiterated%20in%20a%20phone%20call%20with%20Israeli%20PM%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20a%20few%20days%20later.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMore%20than%201%2C400%20were%20killed%20by%20Hamas%20in%20a%20massive%20cross-border%20assault%20into%20southern%20Israel.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20Israel%20bombarded%20Gaza%20strip%20with%20massive%20airstrikes%2C%20which%20have%20killed%20upwards%20of%204%2C000%20people%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20children.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20weeks%20later%2C%20India%20reaffirmed%20support%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20and%20the%20two-state%20solution%20in%20a%20phone%20call%20between%20Modi%20and%20Palestinian%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas%20following%20the%20explosion%20at%20Al-Ahli%20hospital%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20did%20not%20back%20the%20resolution%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-refuses-to-back-landslide-un-general-assembly-call-for-humanitarian-truce-in-gaza%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eabstained%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20the%20voting%20in%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20that%20called%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20truce%20in%20the%20fighting%20to%20allow%20for%20essential%20supplies%20to%20reach%20besieged%20Gaza%20civilians.%20The%20death%20toll%20in%20Gaza%20has%20now%20increased%20to%20over%209000%20in%20three%20weeks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20countries%20outside%20the%20western%20bloc%20which%20has%20not%20used%20the%20term%20ceasefire%20or%20humanitarian%20pause%20for%20the%20current%20violence%20in%20West%20Asia.%20It%20has%20avoided%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98ceasefire%E2%80%99%2C%20while%20saying%20that%20the%20solution%20has%20to%20be%20found%20through%20negotiation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20Jaishankar%20told%20Italian%20lawmakers%20that%20%E2%80%9Cwhat%20happened%20on%20October%207%20was%20a%20big%20act%20of%20terrorism%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20has%20taken%20the%20entire%20region%20into%20a%20different%20direction.%20But%20surely%2C%20it%20must%20be%20everybody%E2%80%99s%20hope%20that%20eventually%E2%80%A6the%20conflict%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20the%20normal%20of%20the%20region%20and%20that%20it%20comes%20back%20to%20some%20stability%2C%20some%20cooperation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20as%20per%20news%20agency%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EANI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStating%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbalance%E2%80%9D%20has%20to%20be%20found%20between%20the%20two%20issues%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20there%20is%20issue%20of%20terrorism%2C%20and%20we%20all%20find%20terrorism%20unacceptable%2C%20we%20have%20to%20stand%20up.%20But%20there%20is%20also%20an%20issue%20of%20Palestine.%20There%20has%20to%20be%20solution%20for%20the%20problems%20faced%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20people%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20reiterated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdialogue%20and%20negotiations%E2%80%9D%20are%20necessary%20to%20find%20a%20way%20out%20of%20the%20current%20crisis.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20view%20is%20that%20it%20has%20to%20be%20a%20two-state%20solution.%20If%20you%20have%20to%20find%20a%20solution%2C%20you%20have%20to%20find%20a%20solution%20through%20dialogue%20and%20negotiation.%20You%20cannot%20find%20a%20solution%20through%20conflict%20and%20terrorism.%20So%20we%20would%20support%20that%20as%20well.%20Given%20the%20current%20situation%E2%80%A6we%20do%20believe%20that%20humanitarian%20law%20must%20be%20respected.%20In%20any%20complex%20situation%2C%20it%20is%20not%20wise%20to%20not%20get%20the%20balance%20right%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInternational%20humanitarian%20law%20has%20strict%20prohibitions%20against%20targeting%20of%20civilians%20in%20a%20conflict%20zone.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699001532000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F30123119%2FUntitled-desi